cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on time-varying networks, which are a type of network architecture. The proposed survivability framework is also evaluated using simulations of a real-world bus communication network. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes two metrics for evaluating the survivability of time-varying networks, and develops several approximation algorithms for computing them. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the modeling of dynamic connectivity in networks, which is a topic of interest in social and information networks. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the survivability properties of time-varying networks, which can be viewed as a type of control system. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new framework for evaluating the survivability of time-varying networks, which can be viewed as a type of information theory problem.
